1
00:00:05,543 --> 00:00:07,296
Dad.

2
00:00:07,380 --> 00:00:10,010
Is this really the road? Yeah.

3
00:00:10,344 --> 00:00:12,432
You got lost, didn't you?

4
00:00:12,974 --> 00:00:17,316
Shut up! The roads in the countryside
are way too dark.

5
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:18,777
Hahahaha...

6
00:00:18,861 --> 00:00:20,489
Ah, Dad! Look out!

7
00:00:20,573 --> 00:00:24,372
Whoa! (Brakes screech)

8
00:00:27,128 --> 00:00:30,259
...Geez. Who parked here?

9
00:00:30,342 --> 00:00:31,636
I'll give them a piece of my mind.

10
00:00:31,720 --> 00:00:33,766
Stop it, Dad.

11
00:00:33,849 --> 00:00:35,478
Uncle, over there. Hmm?

12
00:00:43,202 --> 00:00:44,997
No good. She's dead.

13
00:00:45,080 --> 00:00:46,416
Huh...

14
00:00:46,917 --> 00:00:49,047
Ah, this is...

15
00:00:49,130 --> 00:00:50,216
Huh?

16
00:00:51,510 --> 00:00:53,639
A dying message.

17
00:00:54,390 --> 00:01:00,402
♪~♪

18
00:01:07,375 --> 00:01:10,840
The blackness of shadows, the density of darkness—
the light of reasoning cuts right through them.

19
00:01:10,923 --> 00:01:14,556
An unexpected reaction to the mail.
Expose the whole alibi trick.

20
00:01:14,639 --> 00:01:16,309
See through the one and only truth.

21
00:01:16,393 --> 00:01:18,063
Looks like a kid, but has the mind of an adult.

22
00:01:18,146 --> 00:01:21,069
His name is Detective Conan!

23
00:02:45,752 --> 00:02:51,764
♪~♪

24
00:03:03,036 --> 00:03:06,878
Um, the victim is Hirose Nana-san, 27 years old.

25
00:03:07,462 --> 00:03:10,217
She's an insurance saleswoman living nearby.

26
00:03:10,301 --> 00:03:13,140
On her way home from work,
she stopped by this park,

27
00:03:13,223 --> 00:03:15,144
and it seems she was attacked.

28
00:03:15,561 --> 00:03:17,023
Cause of death is asphyxiation

29
00:03:17,106 --> 00:03:18,484
due to neck compression.

30
00:03:18,567 --> 00:03:19,945
The culprit carefully—

31
00:03:20,279 --> 00:03:22,951
strangled the victim's neck multiple times.

32
00:03:23,452 --> 00:03:26,918
There were multiple overlapping
strangulation marks on her neck.

33
00:03:27,001 --> 00:03:29,130
And the estimated time of death?

34
00:03:29,214 --> 00:03:33,013
Ah, between 10:00 PM and 10:30 PM.

35
00:03:33,347 --> 00:03:35,852
That was shortly before we came here.

36
00:03:36,311 --> 00:03:39,108
Are you sure you didn't see anything?

37
00:03:39,192 --> 00:03:41,154
Yes, sorry.

38
00:03:41,488 --> 00:03:44,077
If we had seen something,
we would've said so by now.

39
00:03:44,160 --> 00:03:45,579
That's true.

40
00:03:45,663 --> 00:03:48,168
But it's okay. The victim conveniently

41
00:03:48,252 --> 00:03:51,341
left us a dying message.

42
00:03:52,051 --> 00:03:55,809
So the culprit's name starts with "Na."

43
00:03:56,351 --> 00:03:59,859
Ah, come to think of it,
the victim's name is also Nana.

44
00:03:59,942 --> 00:04:04,617
Ah, I see! The culprit is herself.
So it's suicide.

45
00:04:04,702 --> 00:04:07,415
The victim must have had a split personality.

46
00:04:07,498 --> 00:04:08,751
Hahaha...

47
00:04:08,835 --> 00:04:12,926
But still, this character looks strange.

48
00:04:14,972 --> 00:04:16,934
And this smell...

49
00:04:17,018 --> 00:04:19,815
No, Conan-kun. Don't get close to the body.

50
00:04:20,149 --> 00:04:22,445
Hey, from this lady's clothes—

51
00:04:22,528 --> 00:04:25,117
There's a strange smell. Huh?

52
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,455
(Sniffing sound) Ah, you're right.

53
00:04:27,538 --> 00:04:29,584
(Sniffing sound) It smells like gunpowder.

54
00:04:29,667 --> 00:04:31,714
Why don't you have the forensics team check it?

55
00:04:31,797 --> 00:04:34,260
Ugh, I was just about to...

56
00:04:34,344 --> 00:04:38,686
Huh? Her face is wet,
and her makeup is a little smeared.

57
00:04:39,395 --> 00:04:41,024
I was just about to check that too...

58
00:04:41,107 --> 00:04:42,652
Nana! Huh?

59
00:04:42,736 --> 00:04:46,409
Nana! Please let go... Nana!

60
00:04:46,994 --> 00:04:48,038
Who might you be?

61
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:51,586
Well... he seems to know the victim.

62
00:04:56,388 --> 00:04:58,350
My name is Samon Osamu.

63
00:04:58,433 --> 00:05:01,356
I work as an primary school teacher.

64
00:05:01,732 --> 00:05:04,404
And what is your relationship
with the victim, Hirose-san?

65
00:05:04,487 --> 00:05:05,489
Yes.

66
00:05:06,408 --> 00:05:09,497
She and I were engaged.

67
00:05:09,915 --> 00:05:11,251
I see.

68
00:05:11,334 --> 00:05:15,426
So, has Hirose-san shown
any unusual behavior lately?

69
00:05:15,509 --> 00:05:20,019
Actually, Nana and I had plans
to have dinner together tonight,

70
00:05:20,436 --> 00:05:23,684
and then I received this email from Nana.

71
00:05:23,684 --> 00:05:29,000
"I'm going to be a little late
because I'm talking with Migita at the park. — Nana"

72
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:32,794
The received time is 9:45 PM.

73
00:05:32,878 --> 00:05:35,800
That's a little before the estimated time of death.

74
00:05:35,884 --> 00:05:37,763
And who is this "Migita"?

75
00:05:38,723 --> 00:05:41,812
He's a man who dated Nana before me.

76
00:05:42,146 --> 00:05:46,571
Migita kept pestering her,
trying to get back together with Nana.

77
00:05:46,654 --> 00:05:50,662
So I thought, maybe...

78
00:05:50,662 --> 00:05:59,305
I see! I've got it! That's "Migita" written with the "migi" of "migi-hidari"
and the "ta" of "tambo", right?

79
00:05:59,388 --> 00:06:01,936
Huh? Yes, that's right, but...

80
00:06:02,353 --> 00:06:06,444
So the victim wasn't writing
the katakana character "Na."

81
00:06:02,353 --> 00:06:06,444
So the victim wasn't writing
the katakana character "Na."

82
00:06:06,987 --> 00:06:11,538
She was trying to write the kanji
character for "right" and ran out of strength.

83
00:06:11,914 --> 00:06:14,585
I see. As expected of Mouri-san.

84
00:06:14,669 --> 00:06:16,548
Neeheeheeheehee!

85
00:06:19,512 --> 00:06:22,101
Anyway, let's go to Migita's place.

86
00:06:22,184 --> 00:06:24,272
Please let me come along too.

87
00:06:24,355 --> 00:06:26,025
Well, but...

88
00:06:26,401 --> 00:06:29,825
Please. I want to help with the investigation
as much as I can.

89
00:06:31,077 --> 00:06:32,580
Oh, all right.

90
00:06:32,998 --> 00:06:36,045
Just please don't get in the way
of the investigation.

91
00:06:36,129 --> 00:06:37,590
Got it.

92
00:06:44,980 --> 00:06:46,942
Are those your students, Sensei?

93
00:06:47,026 --> 00:06:51,451
Yeah. Today, they threw me
an engagement party.

94
00:06:51,785 --> 00:06:53,455
They're good kids, aren't they?

95
00:06:53,538 --> 00:06:54,833
Yes.

96
00:06:54,917 --> 00:06:57,964
I don't know what to tell them either...

97
00:06:58,048 --> 00:07:00,803
Ah. You noticed?

98
00:07:00,887 --> 00:07:05,270
Yes. If I tried to write my name, "Samon,"

99
00:07:05,730 --> 00:07:08,276
it would also become that dying message.

100
00:07:08,652 --> 00:07:11,324
Huh? (Clears throat)

101
00:07:11,407 --> 00:07:14,330
Of course. I was well aware of that.

102
00:07:14,413 --> 00:07:16,794
That you are also a suspect.

103
00:07:16,877 --> 00:07:18,798
Hahahaha...

104
00:07:22,400 --> 00:07:26,521
Ugh!?! Are you serious?

105
00:07:26,897 --> 00:07:30,697
Yes, in the park where you were
supposed to meet her tonight.

106
00:07:31,364 --> 00:07:34,620
Don't screw with me! We never made plans to meet.

107
00:07:35,122 --> 00:07:37,668
Then what is this email?

108
00:07:38,128 --> 00:07:40,215
I don't know anything about that.

109
00:07:40,299 --> 00:07:44,181
She probably used it as an excuse
to meet some other guy.

110
00:07:44,598 --> 00:07:46,436
That's not all.

111
00:07:46,519 --> 00:07:49,860
The victim left us something.

112
00:07:49,943 --> 00:07:52,448
It's called a dying message.

113
00:07:52,991 --> 00:07:56,414
The victim was trying to write your name,
Migita-san,

114
00:07:56,749 --> 00:07:58,919
but ran out of strength.

115
00:07:59,963 --> 00:08:02,426
No, that's not necessarily true.

116
00:08:02,886 --> 00:08:06,434
Nana might have been trying
to write "migi" (右),

117
00:08:06,517 --> 00:08:07,603
Ah.

118
00:08:08,021 --> 00:08:10,902
But it could also be the katakana "na" (ナ),

119
00:08:11,361 --> 00:08:14,408
or the kanji for "big" (大) or "dog" (犬).

120
00:08:14,868 --> 00:08:16,287
Hmm, that's true.

121
00:08:16,621 --> 00:08:20,087
Yeah, yeah. If she was trying to write
that Samon guy's name,

122
00:08:20,797 --> 00:08:22,007
it would look like this too.

123
00:08:22,132 --> 00:08:24,220
Oh, you're right. Hmm...

124
00:08:24,971 --> 00:08:28,771
Besides, it's impossible for me
to have committed the crime.

125
00:08:28,854 --> 00:08:30,983
I have a perfect alibi.

126
00:08:31,401 --> 00:08:32,486
Hmm...

127
00:08:35,868 --> 00:08:38,999
I was working here all night.

128
00:08:39,583 --> 00:08:42,297
That should be recorded
on the security cameras too.

129
00:08:44,552 --> 00:08:48,143
It's around here. I'm glad I had the security system installed.

130
00:08:48,643 --> 00:08:51,065
It's true. You're on camera the whole time.

131
00:08:51,149 --> 00:08:53,319
Ah, you left the frame.

132
00:08:55,240 --> 00:08:56,325
Ah.

133
00:08:56,409 --> 00:08:59,331
What? You came right back.

134
00:08:59,415 --> 00:09:01,502
Even I need to go to the bathroom sometimes.

135
00:09:01,586 --> 00:09:03,674
...Geez. That's confusing.

136
00:09:09,143 --> 00:09:13,401
I see. So the only time Migita-san
wasn't on camera

137
00:09:13,485 --> 00:09:16,199
was the single time he went to the bathroom.

138
00:09:16,574 --> 00:09:21,459
It's about a 20-minute round trip by car
from here to the crime scene.

139
00:09:21,542 --> 00:09:23,588
So committing the crime would be impossible.

140
00:09:23,671 --> 00:09:26,427
Hmph. See? I told you so.

141
00:09:26,511 --> 00:09:27,931
I have a perfect alibi.

142
00:09:28,014 --> 00:09:29,391
I do. Hmph.

143
00:09:29,809 --> 00:09:33,358
At first glance, it certainly looks
like a perfect alibi.

144
00:09:33,441 --> 00:09:35,153
But what about that earlier?

145
00:09:35,654 --> 00:09:40,330
I see. Then the culprit is Samon-san.

146
00:09:40,413 --> 00:09:41,792
It's you.

147
00:09:41,875 --> 00:09:46,092
Why would you say that?
There's no way I would kill Nana.

148
00:09:46,467 --> 00:09:50,600
I didn't even meet with Nana at all today.

149
00:09:50,685 --> 00:09:52,814
Then do you have an alibi?

150
00:09:52,897 --> 00:09:54,108
Well, that's...

151
00:09:54,441 --> 00:09:57,907
It's also possible that you faked that email

152
00:09:57,991 --> 00:10:00,453
to frame Migita-san.

153
00:10:00,537 --> 00:10:02,457
Huh? That's...

154
00:10:02,834 --> 00:10:07,467
No. The dying message points to Migita-san.

155
00:10:07,551 --> 00:10:11,977
And there's that footage too...
But that alone isn't enough evidence.

156
00:10:16,068 --> 00:10:17,404
Hmm...

157
00:10:19,826 --> 00:10:20,870
Ah.

158
00:10:25,587 --> 00:10:28,593
Could this be...

159
00:10:38,948 --> 00:10:43,082
Anyway, we'll hear the details at the station.

160
00:10:43,416 --> 00:10:45,879
But... I didn't do it.

161
00:10:45,962 --> 00:10:48,802
There, there. All the culprits say that.

162
00:10:49,303 --> 00:10:50,722
N... no, I...

163
00:10:50,806 --> 00:10:52,184
Hmph. Let's go, let's go.

164
00:10:52,267 --> 00:10:55,649
No, so I...

165
00:10:56,400 --> 00:11:01,034
Whoa! Wahoo! Hohaha~

166
00:11:01,119 --> 00:11:03,790
Oh my. Could this be...

167
00:11:04,375 --> 00:11:06,254
Sleeping Kogoro!

168
00:11:06,337 --> 00:11:07,422
Dad.

169
00:11:08,006 --> 00:11:13,640
The victim's dying message was not pointing to Samon

170
00:11:14,110 --> 00:11:16,005
It was pointing to you, Migita-san.

171
00:11:16,190 --> 00:11:19,780
Huh? Hmph. How can you say that for sure?

172
00:11:20,115 --> 00:11:23,078
M... Mouri-san.
It's true that with just this,

173
00:11:23,163 --> 00:11:26,294
we can't tell if she was trying
to write "right" or "left."

174
00:11:26,377 --> 00:11:29,300
You can tell exactly which one it was. Hey, Conan.

175
00:11:29,633 --> 00:11:31,052
Okay!

176
00:11:31,137 --> 00:11:33,308
Samon-san, here. Hmm?

177
00:11:33,683 --> 00:11:36,981
Samon-san, you're an primary school teacher, right?

178
00:11:37,064 --> 00:11:39,987
So write "right" so everyone can see.

179
00:11:40,070 --> 00:11:42,117
Huh? Ah...

180
00:11:46,041 --> 00:11:50,550
Oh, so for "right," the stroke order
is the diagonal stroke first, then the horizontal.

181
00:11:50,634 --> 00:11:52,554
Wha... Ah.

182
00:11:52,638 --> 00:11:55,185
Ah... Huh?

183
00:11:55,936 --> 00:11:59,652
Look at the part where the diagonal stroke
and the horizontal stroke intersect.

184
00:11:59,735 --> 00:12:04,245
You can clearly see that the horizontal stroke
was written after the diagonal one.

185
00:12:04,578 --> 00:12:07,209
I... indeed. That's exactly what happened.

186
00:12:07,626 --> 00:12:10,548
It's not the katakana "Na" or the kanji for "left."

187
00:12:10,632 --> 00:12:14,431
That stroke order is only possible
when writing the kanji for "right."

188
00:12:14,765 --> 00:12:17,688
Th... that alone isn't evidence.

189
00:12:17,771 --> 00:12:19,775
And did you forget?

190
00:12:19,858 --> 00:12:21,904
I have a perfect alibi.

191
00:12:22,239 --> 00:12:24,451
That's right. Migita-san was

192
00:12:24,535 --> 00:12:27,124
on the security camera the whole time.

193
00:12:27,207 --> 00:12:30,422
That's true, as long as the security camera
was running.

194
00:12:30,505 --> 00:12:32,091
Huh? Ah.

195
00:12:32,175 --> 00:12:34,346
Ah... Yes.

196
00:12:34,430 --> 00:12:35,890
People tend to assume

197
00:12:35,974 --> 00:12:39,732
that a security camera is always
running continuously.

198
00:12:39,815 --> 00:12:42,237
Migita-san took advantage of that.

199
00:12:42,696 --> 00:12:46,245
That one time you said you went to the bathroom,

200
00:12:46,329 --> 00:12:49,000
you actually turned off the security camera.

201
00:12:51,630 --> 00:12:55,472
Then you took 10 minutes to reach the crime scene
on your scooter,

202
00:12:55,555 --> 00:12:57,517
and killed Nana-san.

203
00:12:57,601 --> 00:13:00,982
(Heavy breathing)

204
00:13:01,442 --> 00:13:04,782
Then, after another 10 minutes,
you came back, Migita-san,

205
00:13:05,116 --> 00:13:08,247
turned the security camera back on,

206
00:13:08,831 --> 00:13:12,130
and returned to the camera's field of view.

207
00:13:12,839 --> 00:13:13,966
Hmm...

208
00:13:14,050 --> 00:13:18,267
That's how you made a recording that was
actually missing over 20 minutes

209
00:13:18,351 --> 00:13:21,774
look like it was continuous.

210
00:13:22,192 --> 00:13:24,154
This store's security camera

211
00:13:24,238 --> 00:13:26,951
doesn't have a time stamp display.

212
00:13:27,076 --> 00:13:28,788
So it was easy to fake.

213
00:13:29,248 --> 00:13:31,627
So you really are the one who killed Nana...

214
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:33,881
Then... evidence?

215
00:13:33,965 --> 00:13:36,470
Where is the evidence that I did it?

216
00:13:36,971 --> 00:13:39,476
You can come in now.

217
00:13:42,315 --> 00:13:45,155
This is a student who lives nearby.

218
00:13:45,905 --> 00:13:48,995
Would you tell us what you witnessed?

219
00:13:49,078 --> 00:13:53,003
Ye... yes. It was around 10:30.

220
00:13:53,504 --> 00:13:56,469
I was about to turn on the TV
because my show was starting.

221
00:13:56,552 --> 00:13:57,804
(Brakes squeal) Then...

222
00:13:57,888 --> 00:14:00,058
(Crash) Ah, huh?

223
00:14:02,189 --> 00:14:03,274
Ah!

224
00:14:03,691 --> 00:14:04,735
Huh?

225
00:14:04,818 --> 00:14:06,947
(Engine sound)

226
00:14:09,411 --> 00:14:12,667
I see. That's definitely 10:30 PM today.

227
00:14:13,084 --> 00:14:16,007
Probably a drunk driver's car.

228
00:14:16,090 --> 00:14:18,763
We should find it if we search around here.

229
00:14:18,846 --> 00:14:22,437
A white car with a broken headlight.

230
00:14:22,979 --> 00:14:26,654
The sound would have been very loud
inside the store too.

231
00:14:26,737 --> 00:14:28,991
But in that footage, you never reacted to it.

232
00:14:28,991 --> 00:14:31,330
But in that footage, you never reacted to it.

233
00:14:31,413 --> 00:14:32,874
Why is that?

234
00:14:33,251 --> 00:14:36,465
Because the footage from that time is missing.

235
00:14:36,549 --> 00:14:39,095
10:30 is the time of the murder.

236
00:14:39,429 --> 00:14:44,606
Migita-san, you weren't in this store
at that time.

237
00:14:44,845 --> 00:14:49,616
Damn it. I thought I had fooled everyone.

238
00:14:50,075 --> 00:14:51,245
It's your hair.

239
00:14:51,328 --> 00:14:53,749
Huh? My hair...

240
00:14:54,167 --> 00:14:58,008
When you left the security camera's view,
your curly hair was sticking up.

241
00:14:58,091 --> 00:15:01,682
But when you came back, it was flat.

242
00:15:01,765 --> 00:15:05,273
Just like when you've been wearing a helmet.

243
00:15:05,648 --> 00:15:09,781
When I saw that, I realized the trick.

244
00:15:13,331 --> 00:15:15,793
It's her fault... Nana's fault.

245
00:15:16,337 --> 00:15:20,010
She kept sending me images like this to harass me.

246
00:15:20,762 --> 00:15:21,930
Damn it.

247
00:15:28,527 --> 00:15:32,494
And on top of that, that woman would say,
"I never did that,"

248
00:15:32,577 --> 00:15:35,124
and make a fool of me.

249
00:15:37,629 --> 00:15:40,008
I knew it. Now the rest...

250
00:15:40,092 --> 00:15:42,389
(Cell phone rings)

251
00:15:42,472 --> 00:15:43,641
Hello?

252
00:15:44,101 --> 00:15:45,895
Huh? Gunshot residue?

253
00:15:45,978 --> 00:15:47,190
Hmph.

254
00:15:47,273 --> 00:15:51,532
It's fine, it's fine. We've already
arrested the culprit. Good work.

255
00:15:51,615 --> 00:15:53,202
Good work.

256
00:15:53,536 --> 00:15:57,794
Did gunshot residue come from the victim's clothes?

257
00:15:57,877 --> 00:15:59,756
Huh? How did you know?

258
00:16:00,090 --> 00:16:02,721
Good. Now it all fits together.

259
00:16:02,804 --> 00:16:06,270
That's the stuff that appears
when you fire a gun, right?

260
00:16:06,353 --> 00:16:09,943
Yes, but? Hey, I never used a gun.

261
00:16:10,319 --> 00:16:14,619
I know. The victim's cause of death
was strangulation.

262
00:16:14,703 --> 00:16:17,751
But then why is there gunshot residue...

263
00:16:18,252 --> 00:16:22,886
It must be some mistake.
I don't think it's related to the case.

264
00:16:22,969 --> 00:16:26,518
Hmm... Oh well, whatever.

265
00:16:26,643 --> 00:16:28,898
Well then, Migita-san, let's head to the station.

266
00:16:28,981 --> 00:16:30,693
Wait, please.

267
00:16:30,777 --> 00:16:32,781
The case isn't over yet.

268
00:16:32,864 --> 00:16:35,244
What are you talking about, Mouri-san?

269
00:16:35,703 --> 00:16:37,665
The culprit is right here,

270
00:16:37,749 --> 00:16:43,427
Of course, Migita-san is the culprit.
He attempted to kill Nana-san.

271
00:16:43,511 --> 00:16:46,934
Huh? "Attempted to kill"? Then...

272
00:16:47,017 --> 00:16:49,940
Yes. The real culprit is someone else.

273
00:16:50,023 --> 00:16:51,360
Huh?

274
00:16:51,443 --> 00:16:54,282
The real culprit who killed Hirose Nana-san—

275
00:16:54,699 --> 00:16:58,707
it's you, Samon Osamu-san.

276
00:16:59,167 --> 00:17:00,211
Huh?

277
00:17:00,795 --> 00:17:04,553
Detective, I'm not trying to protect him, but...

278
00:17:04,636 --> 00:17:06,557
I did kill Nana with these hands.

279
00:17:07,183 --> 00:17:11,149
That's right. Besides, the stroke order
of the dying message

280
00:17:11,233 --> 00:17:12,986
pointed to Migita-san.

281
00:17:13,320 --> 00:17:16,493
That very stroke order is what indicates it.

282
00:17:16,577 --> 00:17:19,749
It wasn't Nana-san who wrote the dying message—

283
00:17:19,833 --> 00:17:22,505
it was you, Samon-san.

284
00:17:22,881 --> 00:17:25,344
First, that dying message.

285
00:17:25,428 --> 00:17:28,559
I highly doubt Nana-san wrote it.

286
00:17:29,018 --> 00:17:32,609
Judging from the emails, she always referred
to Migita-san as "Migita"

287
00:17:32,692 --> 00:17:35,448
in katakana.

288
00:17:36,032 --> 00:17:39,164
Would that same Nana-san, at death's door,
suddenly decide to

289
00:17:39,247 --> 00:17:42,044
write Migita-san's name in kanji?

290
00:17:42,503 --> 00:17:45,343
I see. That is certainly unnatural.

291
00:17:45,426 --> 00:17:48,056
But that doesn't mean I wrote it.

292
00:17:48,140 --> 00:17:51,813
No, that possibility is extremely high.

293
00:17:51,897 --> 00:17:53,066
Huh?

294
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:58,118
Recall the stroke order Migita-san used
to write "right."

295
00:17:59,329 --> 00:18:03,837
And the stroke order that the teacher,
Samon-san, used.

296
00:18:04,297 --> 00:18:05,341
Ah!

297
00:18:05,925 --> 00:18:07,804
But I definitely...

298
00:18:08,222 --> 00:18:10,601
Let me explain step by step.

299
00:18:10,685 --> 00:18:13,816
First, Samon-san's plan began with him

300
00:18:13,899 --> 00:18:17,907
sending harassing emails from Nana-san's phone
to Migita-san.

301
00:18:19,327 --> 00:18:20,955
Knowing Migita-san's personality

302
00:18:21,038 --> 00:18:24,254
and his twisted affection for Nana-san,

303
00:18:24,337 --> 00:18:29,054
Samon-san manipulated him into killing her.

304
00:18:29,723 --> 00:18:32,562
That's outrageous. Why would you say that?

305
00:18:32,645 --> 00:18:34,566
It's the email's writing style.

306
00:18:34,649 --> 00:18:36,570
Wri... writing style?

307
00:18:37,070 --> 00:18:39,576
The emails that Nana-san herself typed

308
00:18:39,659 --> 00:18:42,206
had no punctuation like dots or circles,

309
00:18:42,290 --> 00:18:46,882
and they always ended with the signature "Nana."

310
00:18:47,216 --> 00:18:51,224
But the emails that angered Migita-san
had punctuation

311
00:18:51,308 --> 00:18:54,355
and, conversely, no "Nana" signature.

312
00:18:54,814 --> 00:18:58,906
You can't easily change
the writing style you always use.

313
00:18:58,989 --> 00:19:00,868
Just like stroke order.

314
00:19:01,620 --> 00:19:04,083
It's clear that someone else wrote them.

315
00:19:04,834 --> 00:19:07,882
And the plan succeeded perfectly.

316
00:19:08,342 --> 00:19:09,886
Just as you intended—

317
00:19:09,969 --> 00:19:15,147
Migita-san's hatred for Nana-san grew,
and he killed her.

318
00:19:15,773 --> 00:19:17,944
When you went to the park to check,

319
00:19:18,027 --> 00:19:22,912
and saw Nana-san collapsed,
you must have been certain.

320
00:19:23,247 --> 00:19:25,668
That your plan had succeeded.

321
00:19:26,043 --> 00:19:29,175
But then, something unexpected happened.

322
00:19:29,926 --> 00:19:31,513
When Migita-san left the scene,

323
00:19:32,181 --> 00:19:35,396
she was probably still in a state of suspended animation.

324
00:19:35,855 --> 00:19:38,025
Nana-san regained consciousness.

325
00:19:38,610 --> 00:19:41,867
At that time, Nana-san washed her face with water

326
00:19:41,950 --> 00:19:44,037
to remove the dirt that had gotten on it.

327
00:19:44,122 --> 00:19:45,583
That's why the victim's face was wet

328
00:19:45,666 --> 00:19:48,547
and her makeup had come off.

329
00:19:48,630 --> 00:19:51,553
And shortly after, she was finished off.

330
00:19:52,471 --> 00:19:54,434
By your hand.

331
00:19:54,517 --> 00:19:59,736
Then, you tried to write "Migita" on the ground
using the victim's finger.

332
00:20:00,529 --> 00:20:04,245
But in the middle of it, you noticed us approaching,

333
00:20:04,329 --> 00:20:07,293
and had no choice but to leave in a hurry.

334
00:20:08,795 --> 00:20:10,966
That is the truth of this case.

335
00:20:12,470 --> 00:20:15,392
It's true that it might be consistent.

336
00:20:15,476 --> 00:20:19,525
But it's all circumstantial evidence.
There's no physical evidence.

337
00:20:19,609 --> 00:20:22,448
There is physical evidence
— Huh?

338
00:20:22,865 --> 00:20:26,206
The gunshot residue found on the victim's clothes.

339
00:20:26,623 --> 00:20:28,126
Gunshot residue...

340
00:20:28,627 --> 00:20:31,466
Why would gunshot residue appear at a scene

341
00:20:31,549 --> 00:20:33,804
where no gun was used?

342
00:20:33,887 --> 00:20:37,853
The answer was in the photo on your smartphone.

343
00:20:37,937 --> 00:20:39,357
What do you mean?

344
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:40,901
In that photo,

345
00:20:40,985 --> 00:20:44,450
you were being celebrated with lots of party poppers.

346
00:20:44,534 --> 00:20:47,248
As you can tell from the sound,
which is like a gunshot,

347
00:20:47,331 --> 00:20:51,631
party poppers that explode gunpowder
show a gunshot residue reaction.

348
00:20:51,715 --> 00:20:54,762
That residue got on your clothes at that time,

349
00:20:55,180 --> 00:20:59,772
and when you strangled Nana-san,
it also got onto her clothes.

350
00:21:00,316 --> 00:21:05,326
If they check, the same gunshot residue
that came from her clothes should appear.

351
00:21:05,951 --> 00:21:07,580
You said earlier

352
00:21:07,663 --> 00:21:10,294
that you didn't even meet Nana-san today.

353
00:21:10,627 --> 00:21:12,340
Can you explain that?

354
00:21:12,423 --> 00:21:15,220
Why would the same gunshot residue appear

355
00:21:15,304 --> 00:21:18,268
on the clothes of you, who didn't meet her,
and on Nana-san's clothes?

356
00:21:20,356 --> 00:21:22,318
How ironic.

357
00:21:22,860 --> 00:21:27,077
That the children's celebration of me
would become evidence.

358
00:21:27,453 --> 00:21:30,292
But why did you kill Nana-san?

359
00:21:30,376 --> 00:21:33,590
You looked so happy in that photo.

360
00:21:34,133 --> 00:21:36,888
The motive was Nana-san breaking off
the engagement.

361
00:21:37,473 --> 00:21:38,767
How did you know that?

362
00:21:39,059 --> 00:21:40,729
The ring.

363
00:21:40,813 --> 00:21:44,278
You're wearing an engagement ring
on the middle finger of your right hand.

364
00:21:44,362 --> 00:21:48,077
But there was no ring on Nana-san's finger.

365
00:21:48,161 --> 00:21:50,165
That's when I realized.

366
00:21:50,249 --> 00:21:53,922
That your feelings were one-sided.

367
00:21:56,177 --> 00:22:00,185
I couldn't stand it.
As long as Nana was alive,

368
00:22:00,269 --> 00:22:03,065
I would continue to feel miserable.

369
00:22:04,193 --> 00:22:07,031
I just couldn't bear it anymore.

370
00:22:07,116 --> 00:22:09,745
(Sobbing)

371
00:22:10,497 --> 00:22:16,509
♪~♪

372
00:23:24,353 --> 00:23:30,115
♪~♪

373
00:23:33,913 --> 00:23:36,001
Are you sure we turn right here?

374
00:23:36,084 --> 00:23:38,214
Yeah, I think it's right.

375
00:23:38,298 --> 00:23:40,427
Hmph. If you say so, then it's left.

376
00:23:40,510 --> 00:23:43,933
That's mean! It's right, right. Definitely right.

377
00:23:44,017 --> 00:23:46,230
No, it's left. Definitely left.

378
00:23:46,314 --> 00:23:47,941
I said right! I said left!

379
00:23:48,025 --> 00:23:52,033
(Arguing) Just pick one already!
I wanna go home!

380
00:23:53,244 --> 00:23:56,083
Welcome to my Cooking Arena!

381
00:23:56,542 --> 00:23:59,005
Heheheh. How's that?

382
00:23:59,089 --> 00:24:00,384
This time too, we've brought in

383
00:24:00,467 --> 00:24:04,892
carefully selected delicacies from all over
the country, so rest assured.

384
00:24:05,811 --> 00:24:07,356
It's the key.

385
00:24:09,067 --> 00:24:10,237
You're not coming in.

386
00:24:10,654 --> 00:24:13,410
Beyond here is our domain.

387
00:24:13,868 --> 00:24:16,499
Today's fruit is...

388
00:24:17,251 --> 00:24:21,003
Next Conan...
"A Treasure Chest Filled with Fruit (Part 1)"

389
00:24:37,535 --> 00:24:39,999
Next! Conan's Hint:
"Padlock"

390
00:24:42,128 --> 00:24:44,174
Next time, an incident at the TV station.

391
00:24:44,257 --> 00:24:45,551
I hope I get to see Yoko-chan.

392
00:24:45,634 --> 00:24:47,096
Whatever you say.
